The man was pulled over in the Port Alfred area over the weekend with Tik found hidden in his vehicle. CAPE TOWN Eastern Cape police have arrested a suspect for being in possession of drugs worth R400,000.The man was pulled over in the Port Alfred area over the weekend. Tik was found hidden in the man s vehicle.The police s Mali Govender says the 49-year-old will appear in the Port Alfred Magistrates court on Tuesday. The total weight of the bags were two kilograms with an estimated street value of about R400,000. 